OL,3,CSister of headteacher who took her own
OL,4,Clife says review a 'missed opportunity'
OL,6,FThe sister of a Reading headteacher,
OL,7,Fwho took her own life following a
OL,8,Fnegative Ofsted inspection, has
OL,9,Fdescribed a review into the council's
OL,10,Frole as her employer as "a missed
OL,11,Fopportunity."
OL,13,FJulia Waters says the report, which
OL,14,Fwas published on Friday (12 July),
OL,15,Ffails to ask key questions about what
OL,16,FReading Borough Council could have
OL,17,Fdone to support her better.
